author: Courier sports staff (noreply@couriernews.com)
title: RHS tennis competes at Greenwood
text: GREENWOOD — The Russellville Cyclones and Lady Cyclones tennis team traveled to Greenwood for their final away match of the year.The Cyclones lost 2-3, while the Lady Cyclones split 2-2.“The team is definitely playing better,” Russellville head coach Bill Rowlett said. “The matches were close. The Cyclones must find a way to win the decisive points.”ResultsKenny Sweeny defeated Peyton Golden (RHS) 6-0, 6-1Siam Hooks (RHS) defeated Johnny Tammaruth 6-4, 6-3Andrew Anderson / Paxton Evans defeated Bryce Johnson / Carter Thessing (RHS) 6-2, 6-3Ethan Walker / Woody Woodring defeated Ryan Harpenau / Zeb Taylor (RHS), 6-0, 6-2Bryce Johnson (RHS) defeated Ethan Walker, 7-5Lady CyclonesSophie Davis (RHS) defeated Darian Wilson, 6-1, 6-2Maebre Hale (RHS) defeated Jenna Rylko, 6-1, 5-7, 7-5Maria Geoly / Lindsey Gills defeated Maebre Hale / Megan Skartvedt (RHS), 6-1, 6-1Kristen Keene / Hailey Rice defeated Paige Havner / Selby Scott (RHS), 6-0, 6-1
